The paper deals with online learning with linear models, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes algorithms that are invariant under arbitrary rescaling of the features, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the runtime performance of the proposed algorithms, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS).
